<TEXT>
   Police were searching for vandals who
left behind a trail of anti-Semitic and racist graffiti through
several miles of this suburban town.
   ``It's rather sad this could happen in 1989 in a town where we
like to think everyone gets along,'' said Detective Jim Fitzgerald.
   The vandalism occurred late Saturday or early Sunday, the eve of
Yom Kippur, the Jewish Day of Atonement.
