<HEAD>Bush's Cyst Non-Cancerous</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cyst removed from President Bush's right
middle finger was non-cancerous, as had been expected, a spokesman
said today.
   The cyst, which had bothered Bush for several years, was removed
during surgery Friday at Walter Reed Army Medical Center and was
tested to make sure it was not cancerous.
   ``The pathology report is (that it is) benign,'' said a press
aide, Laura Melillo.
   She said Bush was informed of the results today as he was
winding up a three-day weekend at Camp David, the presidential
retreat in Maryland's Catoctin Mountains. Bush had described the
surgery, done under a local anesthetic, as minor but said doctors
had had to cut deeply into the finger, near the bone, to remove the
growth.
