<HEAD>Susan Dey Deals with Cancer in New Movie</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs 3rd graf to include that Dey had benign cyst. For release
at 6 p.m. EDT</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Susan Dey, who portrays a woman who dies
needlessly of cervical cancer in a new TV movie, says the role
changed her attitude toward health care.
   ``It made me more positive about participating in it,'' she said
in the November Redbook. ``No offense to doctors, but I've never
liked them. They give bad news. Before I made this movie, if I felt
pain, I'd just sit and suffer.''
   The ``L.A. Law'' star says she once ignored a tumor in her
breast for a year ``until the pain got so bad that I couldn't lift
my arm.'' The problem turned out to be a benign cyst that was
removed.
   But she says she changed her mind after portraying the real-life
story of a woman who didn't learn about her condition until it was
too late, although doctors had warning signs.
   The movie, ``I Love You Perfect,'' should ``make an impact,''
she said. ``It will make women aware that there is a need for the
medical profession in their lives, but that they must participate
in their own health care and not just allow other people to take
over.''
