<HEAD>Stolen Negatives of Eye Patients' Retinas Found</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Film canisters with hundreds of negatives of eye
retinas were found and returned to the photographer Monday, ending
a two-day search after they were stolen from a car, police said.
   Recovery of the canisters, which were in a briefcase stolen from
the photographer's car, means patients won't have to have the
photographs retaken, said a spokeswoman from the Massachusetts Eye
and Ear Infirmary.
