Police are still investigating the robbery, because not all the
missing items have been found.
   Hospital spokewoman Regina Kilfoyle said the film had been
developed and was in fine condition.
   The pictures are made by injecting dye into the body, which
causes small veins in the eye to glow fluorescently, making it
easier to diagnose problems.
