<HEAD>Police: Son Killed Father in Dispute Over Mowing Lawn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A teen-ager was in custody Monday for allegedly
shooting his father to death during a dispute over mowing the lawn.
   The 17-year-old boy's name was not released because of his age,
and investigators were considering charges, said Sgt. Mike Diaz of
the Metro-Dade police homicide squad.
   James Hines, 47, died within minutes of the shooting Sunday.
   Police said Hines had told his son to mow the lawn about noon,
then took a nap.
   When the father awoke just before 4 p.m., he found the lawn
uncut and confronted his son with a stick, Diaz said.
   The father hit the son with the stick, and the boy allegedly
produced a handgun and fired, killing Hines with one shot to the
torso, Diaz said.
   It was not known where the boy got the gun, the officer said.
