<HEAD>French President Overcome by Heat During Ceremony</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Francois Mitterrand of
France was overcome by 90-degree heat Monday at a welcoming
ceremony at the capital's airport, French officials said.
   A French Embassy spokeswoman said the president ``felt
indisposed because of the heat'' but that he ``was all right''
after having rested.
   During the ceremony at Maiquetia airport, the 72-year-old
president slumped heavily against a wall in the hot weather, and
officials rushed to offer the French leader a chair, witnesses said.
   The ceremony was cut short, and Mitterrand left the airport
immediately for downtown. However, he kept up scheduled activities
later in the day, including a meeting with President Carlos Andres
Perez.
   In Guadeloupe in the morning, Mitterrand told victims of
Hurricane Hugo the French Parliament will consider subsidies to
those who lost their homes when Hugo slammed into the
French-governed Caribbean island three weeks ago.
   Mitterrand came to Venezuela on a 48-hour state visit with his
wife, Danielle. He was scheduled to leave for Quito, Ecuador, on
Wednesday.
