<HEAD>Chrysler Announces Incentives on 1990 Models</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HIGHLAND PARK, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chrysler Motors Corp. says it has
revised cash-back incentives offered on 1990 models, ranging from
$300 on base models of the Dodge Shadow and Plymouth Sundance to
$1,000 on larger models and the Dodge ES sports models.
   Chrysler raised the incentive on the Dodge Daytona from $500
offered on the 1988-89 models to $750 on the 1990 model. Incentives
on the Daytona ES and the LeBaron Convertible Premium GT and GTC
are $1,000, which also is $250 higher.
