<FIRST>r f AM-USX-SouthAfrica     10-09 0194</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-USX-South Africa,0202</SECOND>
<HEAD>USX Out of South Africa</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   USX Corp. Monday said it has sold all of its
equity interests in South African companies as part of its
continuing restructuring.
   The oil and steel concern withheld the identify of the buyers
and the sale price.
   USX last week said it was offering to sell the natural gas and
oil reserves of its Texas Oil &amp; Gas Corp. subsidiary, a move that
follows changes in its steel, transportation and diversified
busiesses.
   Shareholders submitted a resolution earlier this year that USX
sell its holdings in the racially segregated nation. They withdrew
the resolution after management said sale negotiations were under
way.
   USX held a 21 percent stake in Associated Manganese Mines of
South Africa Ltd., 45 percent in Feralloys Ltd. and 46 percent in
Prieska Copper Mines Ltd. The companies produce iron ore, manganese
ore, chrome ore, zinc concentrates and ferroalloys.
   The company said it formerly used minerals from the companies
but no longer finds them essential as a supplier. USX had no
operations or employees in South Africa.
   USX had net income $756 million on sales of $17 billion in 1988.
</TEXT>
