<HEAD>Corporate Bond Prices Rise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Corporate bond prices edged higher Monday but
trading was very light as the U.S. market for Treasury issues
closed for the Columbus Day holiday.
   Moody's Investment Grade Corporate Bond Index, which measures
total return on a portfolio of 80 corporate bonds with maturities
of five years or longer, rose 0.08 to finish at 333.58.
   In the tax-exempt market, the Bond Buyer index of 40 actively
traded municipal bonds gained [ point to 9227-32. The average yield
to maturity, which declines when the price rises, slipped to 7.32
percent from 7.33 percent late Friday.
   But the domestic market for Treasury bills, notes and bonds was
closed as were many banks. In Europe, prices of Treasury issues
were slightly higher, according to Telerate Inc., a
financial-information service.
</TEXT>
